      <h1 class='title'>Spending Review 2004: Devolved Administrations Funding Rules</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='lords-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HL Deb 12 July 2004 vol 663 c50WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_50ws' title='Col. 50WS &mdash; HL Deb 12 July 2004 vol 663 c50WS' name='column_50ws' href='#column_50ws' rel='bookmark'>50WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution'>
        <a name='S5LV0663P0_20040712_LWS_3'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-andrew-mcintosh' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S5LV0663P0_20040712_LWS_3' title='Link to this speech by Mr Andrew McIntosh' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-andrew-mcintosh" title="Mr Andrew McIntosh">The Parliamentary Under-Secretary of State, Department for Culture, Media and Sport (Lord McIntosh of Haringey)</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para">My right honourable friend the Chief Secretary to the Treasury (Paul Boateng) has made the following Written Ministerial Statement.</p><p>Copies of the updated Statement of Funding Policy, which sets out the funding arrangements for the devolved administrations, have today been placed in the Libraries of the House.</p>
        </blockquote>
